[1] World update
Date: Fri 20 May 2022
Source: Hindustan Times [edited]
https://www.hindustantimes.com/world-news/monkeypox-alert-nations-where-this-rare-disease-has-been-identified-so-far-list-here-101652978019000-amp.html


Monkeypox: nations where this rare disease has been identified so far
-------------------------------------------------------------
Europe:
- Spain: authorities reported 14 confirmed cases on Friday [20 May 2022], taking the total to 21. There are another 20 suspected cases -- 19 in the central region of Madrid and one in the Canary Islands, Reuters quoted health authorities.
- France has reported its first monkeypox case -- a man from the country's Ile-de-France region, which includes Paris. He had not travelled recently to a country where the virus is currently circulating, health authorities said Friday [20 May 2022].
- Belgium has reported 2 confirmed cases. They live in different cities but were at the same party (at an undisclosed location). Neither is seriously ill, although both are in isolation, AFP said citing Belgian media reports.
- Germany: first case was reported by Reuters, which quoted Focus, a German-language news magazine that, in turn, cited the German military.
- Italy on Thursday [19 May 2022] reported its 1st case.
- Sweden reported its 1st case on Thursday [19 May 2022].
- Portugal has 14 cases so far, with 20 others being monitored.
- In the United Kingdom, 9 cases have been reported since [6 May 2022].

North America:
- Canada has reported 2 cases. At least 17 other suspected cases are under investigation in Montreal [Quebec province], authorities said.
- United States: the state of Massachusetts this week reported a case of monkeypox in a man who had recently travelled to Canada.

Pacific:
- Australian authorities on Friday [20 May 2022] said they had identified a probable case of monkeypox in a traveller from Europe, with confirmatory testing under way.

