******
[5] Spain and Portugal
Date: Fri 20 May 2022
Source: Reuters [edited]
https://www.reuters.com/business/healthcare-pharmaceuticals/spain-reports-14-new-confirmed-monkeypox-cases-total-21-2022-05-20/


Health authorities in Spain reported on Friday [20 May 2022] 24 new confirmed cases of monkeypox, mainly in the Madrid region where the regional government closed a sauna linked to the majority of infections. The total tally in Spain has now reached 30, while 23 confirmed cases have now been identified in neighbouring Portugal, where 9 new cases were detected on Friday [20 May 2022].

Madrid authorities have been working on tracing the cases mainly from a single outbreak in a sauna, regional health chief Enrique Ruiz Escudero told reporters on Friday [20 May 2022]. The word sauna is used in Spain to describe establishments popular with gay men looking for sex rather than just a bathhouse.

"The Public Health Department will carry out an even more detailed analysis... to control contagion, cut the chains of transmission and try to mitigate the transmission of this virus as much as possible," he said.

The Extremadura region confirmed its first case on Friday afternoon [20 May 2022].

Another 18 suspected cases are under investigation in Spain, 15 in the Madrid region, 2 in the Canary Islands and one in Andalusia, the health authorities said.

Spain is assessing different therapeutic options, such as antivirals and vaccines, but so far all cases have mild symptoms and therefore no specific ad hoc treatment has been necessary, Spanish health minister Carolina Darias told reporters on Friday [20 May 2022].

[byline: Emma Pinedo and Patricia Vicente rua]

--
communicated by:
ProMED

[If the suspected cases are confirmed, the widespread and apparently simultaneous occurrence of cases in Spain is remarkably geographically widespread. Contact tracing will be a challenge. - Mod.TY]

******
[6] Sweden
Date: Thu 19 May 2022
Source: The News International [edited]
https://www.thenews.com.pk/latest/959055-sweden-reports-first-case-of-monkeypox


"One person in the Stockholm region has been confirmed to be infected with monkey pox," Sweden's Public Health Agency said in a statement. The infected person "is not seriously ill, but has been given care," according to the agency.

"We still don't know where the person was infected. An investigation is currently under way," Klara Sonden, an infectious disease doctor and investigator at the agency, said in a statement. The health authority said it is now "investigating with the regional infection control centres whether there are more cases in Sweden."

The European Centre for Disease Prevention and Control (ECDC) also said on Thursday [19 May 2022] it expects to publish a first risk assessment report "early next week." The European Union agency, which said it was "monitoring the situation closely", recommends that "suspected cases should be isolated and tested and notified promptly".

