******
[7] Italy
Date: Fri 20 May 2022
Source: Reuters [edited]
https://www.reuters.com/business/healthcare-pharmaceuticals/italy-confirms-two-more-monkeypox-infections-brings-total-cases-three-2022-05-20/


Italy on Friday [20 May 2022] confirmed 2 more cases of monkeypox infection at the Spallanzani hospital in Rome, bringing the total cases to 3 so far in the country. The Lazio region health commissioner Alessio D'Amato said in a statement that the 2 other suspected infections related to the first detected case had now been confirmed. The Spallanzani hospital said on Thursday [19 May 2022] that the first patient with monkeypox, a mild viral infection whose symptoms include fever, headaches as well as a distinctive bumpy rash, had come back to Italy from a stay on the Canary islands.

Andrea Antinori, a doctor at the hospital, which specialises in infectious diseases, said in a news conference that many of the cases reported in Europe had originated through human-to-human transmission. "Our cases confirm this trend," he said, adding that it was too early to say if the illness could be defined as a sexually transmitted disease.

D'Amato said during the news conference that each detected case had come into contact with about 10 people, so screening would concern 30 contacts.

There are 2 main strains [clades]: the Congo strain, which is more severe -- with up to 10% mortality -- and the West African strain, which has a fatality rate of about 1%.

[byline: Federico Maccioni]

